Description: I am trying once again to thin out my herd of stringed instruments. It’s getting harder and harder since I am attached to all of them at this point. This one is a RARE Jay Turser JT-50C custom SG style guitar. This is a top Turser from the heyday of the Chinese factory builds before the move(s) to Viet Nam and Korean factories. This guitar looks, feels and plays like a 2K axe. The finish is a flawless deep wine red. I bought this as a collector and never gigged it out. It has mostly been in a gig bag so the gold hardware is in surprisingly great shape for a 15+ year old instrument. Features: Solid majog body (and I believe neck…not sure). Set neck, bound, with large MOP markers. Triple bound headstock with inlaid dragons eye and signature. All gold hardware in exceptional shape. Grover style tuners. Triple bound pick guard. Wilkinson roller bridge (gold) ($23.95) Silver topped black numbered and named bell knobs ($13.95) Wax potted alnico humbucking gold pickups. *there is 1 small chip at the neck joint in the back…see photo The neck is straight, the action is low, the frets are as new (polished too) the sound is warm clean and overdrives like a true vintage SG. This guitar is a looker, and it is definitely a player. I will be listing about 20 guitars and basses, guitar parts and microphones in the next few months. I ship fast and currently own a 100% feedback rating as a buyer and seller on EBay (860+ transactions, a member since 2001).
Title: Jay Turser JT-50C SG style Custom electric guitar Early Chinese Model!
